We understand the importance of personal information to you and will do our best to protect your personal information. We are committed to maintaining your trust in us, and we promise that we will take appropriate security measures to protect your personal information in accordance with the industry's mature security standards. Please read and understand this policy before using our services.
1. How We Collect and Use Your Personal Information
1.1. Personal information refers to all kinds of information recorded electronically or otherwise that can identify the identity of a specific natural person or reflect the activity of a specific natural person, either alone or in combination with other information. The information after anonymization is not included.
1.2. We collect your information for the following purposes:
(1) To provide, maintain, or improve products or services to you.
(2) Send you important notices.
(3) Activate or verify the product or service.
(4) Carry out promotion and introductionnof products to you as permitted by laws and regulations.
(5) Other uses with your permission.
Before accepting the service, we will show you the information you need to submit through our platform page, which shall prevail. If you do not use some services, you do not need to provide relevant information.
1.3 We will only collect and use your personal information for the following purposes described in this policy:
(1) User registration. To use any of InstaDrum's products and / or services, you must become an official member of InstaDrum. When you register your InstaDrum account or use the products and / or services provided by InstaDrum, you need to provide us with your mobile phone number or email address. We will verify the validity of your identity information by SMS verification code or email verification code. We will encrypt and store these data in a secure server. The mobile phone number or email account you submitted is used to register your account, and as one of the contact methods you specify with us, it is used to receive relevant service notifications (for example, new product launch, activity reminder, service change and service related notifications, we will notify you by SMS, telephone or mail). Mobile phone numbers and email accounts are sensitive information, and such information is collected to meet the requirements of network real name system of relevant laws and regulations; If you do not provide such information, you may not be able to use our services normally.
(2) Personal settings. After you log in, you can complete your personal information in your personal settings: Avatar, nickname, age, etc. we need these data to provide you with relevant services quickly and conveniently, and constantly optimize the service content to better meet your use needs. If you do not provide such information, it will not affect your use of a specific technical service.
(3) App usage. In order to use the app, you need to check whether your device's network, Bluetooth function (blue tooth with drum scene) / USB function (USB cable with drum scene) / microphone function (Drum Recording scene) are normal before use. When using these functions, you need to turn on the Bluetooth function on the device (Bluetooth with drum scene, please note that after Android version 6.0, Bluetooth and device positioning permission are combined into one switch, so turning on Bluetooth function also turns on device positioning permission) / USB function (USB cable with drum scene) / microphone function (Drum Recording scene) By enabling these functions, we will provide you with complete intelligent drum services. In order to provide you with perfect products and / or exclusive services, after obtaining your authorization and consent, we will upload your performance MIDI data and / or recording to a secure server for analysis and calculation, and present you with performance results and detailed reports. Your open of these permissions means we have your authorization to collect and use these personal information to achieve the above functions. You can also turn off the corresponding access rights in the device at any time. If you turn off the rights, you will cancel these authorizations, then we will no longer continue to collect and use your personal information, nor can we provide you with the above functions corresponding to these authorizations. If you continue to use these functions, you need to Reopen access. Your decision to close access will not affect the processing of personal information previously based on your authorization.
(4) Optimize the user experience. We may automatically receive and record information from your device and browser, including your cookie information, your country, regional and language settings, device model, operating system, mobile carrier and software and hardware attributes.
We may use your IP address to provide you with our product on your device, and to help us with server problem diagnosis and to administer the Services. An IP address is a numeric code that identifies your device on a network, or in this case, the Internet.
We may also need to use your IP geolocation data in order to receive your general location and provide you with contents adjusted for your territory. Your IP address is also used to gather broad demographic information.
With your prior consent, we will collect your information or obtain system permissions for the purpose of analyzing your use of our products and / or services, optimizing network quality in different regions and advertising optimization, including:
a) Device or software information, including the configuration information provided by your mobile device, web browser or other programs used to access our products and / or services, the version used by the mobile device, device identification code and other relevant information (IP address, Wi Fi access point, Bluetooth and other information that can provide relevant information);
b) The information you search or browse when using our products and / or services, including the web search words you use, the URL address of the social media page you visit, and other information and content details you browse or require when using our products and / or services;
c) The information (metadata) contained in the content you share through our products and / or services, including the date, time or place of photos, recordings or videos taken or uploaded. You should be aware that the above functions are the extended business services we provide to you. We will open the above functions with your consent. You can choose not to provide us with the personal information related to the implementation of the above functions, or refuse to open the corresponding system permissions. In this case, you will not be able to experience the above services. At the same time, after you enable the above business expansion functions, you can manage, refuse or close relevant permissions through system settings at any time. Closing the permissions means that you have cancelled these authorizations. We will no longer continue to collect and use your personal information, nor can we provide you with the services and / or functions corresponding to this authorization, If you continue to use these functions, you need to turn on access again. Your decision to close the permission will not affect the previous processing of personal information based on your authorization. We hereby guarantee that your failure to select the above extended business functions will not affect your normal use of the basic business functions we provide you.
d) If you contact with our support team regarding issues in our Services or any other issues, we may collect the information regarding your interactions with us, in order to help us provide a better service.
e) We also store all messages sent to our forums to help users find useful information about the Services.
(5) For your account security, we will establish an InstaDrum user center, and the following information you provide on our platform will be synchronized to the InstaDrum user center:
a) The types of synchronized information include: mobile phone number, email address, avatar, nickname, age, etc. you use when registering on our platform;
b) Synchronized applications include: InstaDrum;
(6) In order to provide you with more professional and secure basic business functions and additional business functions, we will access the third-party software development kit (SDK) for technical needs. The SDK technical service provider will obtain corresponding permissions and information based on the functions or services provided to you. Please read our SDK list below in detail to learn about our specific integrated SDK name, SDK technical service provider, SDK application scenario (i.e. SDK type), permissions and personal information types obtained by the SDK. We have conducted security monitoring on the SDK integrated in this software to protect your personal information security. After you click agree to this policy, you also authorize and agree the SDK technical service provider to obtain and process your permissions and information according to the following table. You can view the data use and protection rules of third parties through relevant links. Please note that the personal information processing type of the third-party SDK may change due to version upgrade, policy adjustment and other reasons. Please refer to the official instructions published by the third-party SDK
